# AGENTS.md — ${PROJECT_NAME}

## Hyperflow

This project uses **hyperflow v${HYPERFLOW_VERSION}** for autonomous multi-agent orchestration.

**Activation:** On session start, load and follow the `hyperflow` skill. If you do not have access to the skill mechanism, read `~/.hyperflow/config.json` for model routing and follow the 9-layer protocol documented at https://github.com/Mohammed-Abdelhady/hyperflow.

**Behavior overrides:**
- Decompose every task into worker subtasks (parallel where independent)
- Thinking-tier model reviews every worker output before it is considered done
- Print agent labels (`⚡ [Role] description`) before each dispatch
- Print a usage summary at task end

**Project context (read on session start):**
- `.hyperflow/profile.md` — project identity and tech stack
- `.hyperflow/architecture.md` — folder structure
- `.hyperflow/conventions.md` — coding conventions and naming
- `.hyperflow/dependencies.md` — dependency map
- `.hyperflow/testing.md` — test framework and patterns
- `.hyperflow/git-workflow.md` — branching and release process

**Persistent memory (project-scoped):**
- `.hyperflow/memory/index.md` — searchable index of past learnings
- `.hyperflow/memory/learnings.md` — patterns and gotchas
- `.hyperflow/memory/decisions.md` — architectural decisions
- `.hyperflow/memory/pitfalls.md` — failed approaches and why
- `.hyperflow/memory/patterns.md` — reusable patterns
- `.hyperflow/memory/conventions.md` — project-specific conventions

**Active work:**
- `.hyperflow/tasks/` — in-progress task tracking

After each batch of worker outputs, append durable learnings to `.hyperflow/memory/` using the tagged entry format documented in the hyperflow skill.

